1
00:00:11,087 --> 00:00:13,423
[speaking Japanese]

2
00:00:32,760 --> 00:00:34,361
[Blackthorne] <i>I'm assuming
that man's your husband.</i>

3
00:00:34,362 --> 00:00:35,729
[Mariko]
<i>His name is Toda Hirokatsu,</i>

4
00:00:35,730 --> 00:00:36,797
though friends call him Buntaro.

5
00:00:38,299 --> 00:00:39,267
For Christ's sake,
he can still make it.

6
00:00:39,268 --> 00:00:41,335
[men shouting]

7
00:00:42,403 --> 00:00:44,071
Toda Hirokatsu!

8
00:00:48,332 --> 00:00:49,465
[Blackthorne]
<i>Shit.</i>

9
00:00:49,466 --> 00:00:51,234
[Mariko]
Sorry.

10
00:00:51,235 --> 00:00:52,502
I'm happy to see
you have changed your mind

11
00:00:52,503 --> 00:00:53,670
about bathing.

12
00:00:53,671 --> 00:00:56,139
<i>You seem in good spirits.</i>

13
00:00:56,140 --> 00:00:57,573
[Blackthorne]
<i>After a night of good company.</i>

14
00:00:57,574 --> 00:00:59,342
The courtesan
was acceptable, then.

15
00:01:01,211 --> 00:01:02,345
Nebara Jozen!

16
00:01:06,383 --> 00:01:07,484
[shouts]

17
00:01:10,587 --> 00:01:12,622
[grunting]

18
00:01:32,309 --> 00:01:34,344
[distant rumbling]

19
00:01:36,780 --> 00:01:39,316
[horses neighing]

20
00:01:45,255 --> 00:01:48,491
[man shouting in distance]

21
00:01:57,234 --> 00:01:59,269
♪ ♪

22
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:07,577
[man yells in distance]

23
00:02:35,272 --> 00:02:38,308
♪ ♪

24
00:03:06,737 --> 00:03:09,773
♪ ♪

25
00:03:39,202 --> 00:03:42,205
♪ ♪

26
00:04:10,534 --> 00:04:12,569
♪ ♪

27
00:05:28,478 --> 00:05:29,779
[scoffs]

28
00:05:43,827 --> 00:05:46,062
♪ ♪

29
00:05:47,798 --> 00:05:49,532
[sighs]

30
00:06:16,893 --> 00:06:19,496
[coughs]

31
00:06:31,808 --> 00:06:33,843
[Sugiyama coughing]

32
00:06:54,264 --> 00:06:56,299
[indistinct shouting
in distance]

33
00:07:47,584 --> 00:07:48,618
Hmm.

34
00:08:12,175 --> 00:08:13,376
[exhales]

35
00:10:19,469 --> 00:10:20,503
[speaks Japanese]

36
00:10:31,882 --> 00:10:34,084
♪ ♪

37
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,128
[rain pattering]

38
00:10:45,129 --> 00:10:47,197
[thunder rumbling]

39
00:10:57,207 --> 00:10:59,809
[thunder rumbling]

40
00:11:38,782 --> 00:11:40,149
As I live and breathe.

41
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:41,184
The most precious gift there is.

42
00:11:41,185 --> 00:11:42,518
You see that?

43
00:11:42,519 --> 00:11:44,120
I do my part,
and the old man does his.

44
00:11:44,121 --> 00:11:45,788
Now we're getting somewhere.

45
00:11:45,789 --> 00:11:47,290
You can't understand a word
I'm saying,

46
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:48,591
but when I was your age,

47
00:11:48,592 --> 00:11:50,426
one of my first chores
was cleaning game

48
00:11:50,427 --> 00:11:51,861
my father would poach
from an estate in Chatham.

49
00:11:51,862 --> 00:11:53,129
Watch this.

50
00:11:54,431 --> 00:11:56,532
Now, we'll hang it up

51
00:11:56,533 --> 00:11:57,834
for a few days to mature,
maybe a week,

52
00:11:57,835 --> 00:12:00,803
depending on the weather.

53
00:12:00,804 --> 00:12:02,372
There we are.

54
00:12:14,851 --> 00:12:18,788
Yes, yes. There will be
a terrible stench.

55
00:12:18,789 --> 00:12:20,790
But this is a gift
from Toranaga-sama.

56
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:23,593
It must be the best pheasant
this village has ever prepared.

57
00:12:23,594 --> 00:12:27,430
Now, this next part
is very important.

58
00:12:27,431 --> 00:12:30,367
No one is to touch this bird.

59
00:12:35,372 --> 00:12:36,406
Um...

60
00:13:06,436 --> 00:13:08,505
♪ ♪

61
00:14:37,294 --> 00:14:39,362
♪ ♪

62
00:15:04,354 --> 00:15:06,656
[grunts]

63
00:16:06,917 --> 00:16:09,119
[groans]

64
00:16:29,439 --> 00:16:30,573
[laughs softly]

65
00:16:40,384 --> 00:16:42,085
[grunts]

66
00:17:23,560 --> 00:17:26,496
[Yabushige grunting angrily]

67
00:17:28,899 --> 00:17:30,533
[grumbling]

68
00:17:47,884 --> 00:17:49,286
[Omi exhales]

69
00:18:07,771 --> 00:18:09,172
[Yabushige exhales]

70
00:18:16,780 --> 00:18:18,181
Huh?

71
00:18:20,884 --> 00:18:22,118
[laughs softly]

72
00:18:24,821 --> 00:18:26,523
Oh?

73
00:18:31,428 --> 00:18:33,797
Huh? Huh?

74
00:18:37,868 --> 00:18:39,369
[exhales]

75
00:18:52,649 --> 00:18:54,651
[insects buzzing]

76
00:19:21,378 --> 00:19:22,579
[exhales]

77
00:20:05,222 --> 00:20:06,423
[grunts softly]

78
00:20:08,425 --> 00:20:11,161
I understand your husband
is to stay with us now.

79
00:20:14,331 --> 00:20:17,533
Is there anything you feel I...

80
00:20:17,534 --> 00:20:19,569
should be preparing for?

81
00:20:20,704 --> 00:20:23,773
- Dinner?
- Dinner.

82
00:20:28,445 --> 00:20:30,814
And you will be a gracious host.

83
00:20:53,170 --> 00:20:54,771
[grunting]

84
00:21:29,239 --> 00:21:31,140
[Mariko]
My husband wishes for you

85
00:21:31,141 --> 00:21:33,276
to address him as Toda-sama,

86
00:21:33,277 --> 00:21:36,246
as Buntaro is reserved only
for those close to him.

87
00:21:37,647 --> 00:21:41,417
Tell Toda-sama it's a relief
he was able to escape Osaka

88
00:21:41,418 --> 00:21:43,119
and an honor for him
to have observed

89
00:21:43,120 --> 00:21:44,621
our cannon regiment today.

90
00:21:49,159 --> 00:21:51,227
[insect buzzing]

91
00:21:59,569 --> 00:22:01,704
He believes that,
in the hands of a true samurai,

92
00:22:01,705 --> 00:22:04,274
the bow and sword will always
outmatch the cannon.

93
00:22:05,442 --> 00:22:07,143
Oh. Well, perhaps

94
00:22:07,144 --> 00:22:08,811
we should have
a friendly contest sometime.

95
00:22:08,812 --> 00:22:10,313
[insect buzzes]

96
00:22:10,314 --> 00:22:12,415
[buzzing stops]

97
00:22:12,416 --> 00:22:14,150
[sniffs]

98
00:22:27,130 --> 00:22:28,665
[Blackthorne]
Now, for my esteemed guests

99
00:22:28,666 --> 00:22:31,567
on this wonderful evening,
I am proud to present to you

100
00:22:31,568 --> 00:22:33,536
a taste from my home country.

101
00:22:33,537 --> 00:22:37,273
We call it English rabbit stew.

102
00:22:37,274 --> 00:22:38,775
Now, admittedly,

103
00:22:38,776 --> 00:22:40,176
I had to substitute
a few of the ingredients...

104
00:22:40,177 --> 00:22:41,577
sake for sherry,
a few other things...

105
00:22:41,578 --> 00:22:43,279
but that's
the beauty of a good stew.

106
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:45,782
It all tastes
like gravy in the end.

107
00:22:51,288 --> 00:22:52,489
<i>Mariko-sama wa?</i>

108
00:22:54,291 --> 00:22:57,360
We are particular eaters,
Anjin-sama.

109
00:22:57,361 --> 00:22:58,762
It is our loss.

110
00:23:04,167 --> 00:23:06,636
It's not the same
without sherry anyway.

111
00:23:06,637 --> 00:23:08,672
There you go.

112
00:23:11,575 --> 00:23:14,411
Oh, please. Eat.

113
00:23:25,422 --> 00:23:26,790
[chuckles]

114
00:23:34,698 --> 00:23:35,798
What did he say?

115
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:37,300
My husband comments

116
00:23:37,301 --> 00:23:39,836
on the way you eat your noodles.

117
00:23:39,837 --> 00:23:41,404
The sound you make while eating

118
00:23:41,405 --> 00:23:43,172
reveals the depth
of your pleasure.

119
00:23:43,173 --> 00:23:45,475
[laughs]

120
00:23:49,579 --> 00:23:51,281
[slurps]

121
00:23:54,551 --> 00:23:56,486
[slurping]

122
00:23:57,721 --> 00:23:59,122
Hmm.

123
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:04,361
[liquid pours]

124
00:24:11,568 --> 00:24:13,403
You know, where I come from,
only women

125
00:24:13,404 --> 00:24:15,505
drink from a tiny cup like that.

126
00:24:24,848 --> 00:24:27,617
The polite size
of the sake cup helps us

127
00:24:27,618 --> 00:24:30,220
- to enjoy the drink and...
- [clatters]

128
00:24:40,163 --> 00:24:42,532
This is how we drink.

129
00:24:42,533 --> 00:24:45,368
[slurping]

130
00:25:03,720 --> 00:25:05,455
[sets down bottle]

131
00:25:08,291 --> 00:25:10,627
[slurping]

132
00:25:14,564 --> 00:25:17,467
[both slurping]

133
00:25:21,138 --> 00:25:22,639
[exhales]

134
00:25:23,740 --> 00:25:25,375
[exhales]

135
00:25:42,859 --> 00:25:45,395
[Blackthorne] Seeing as we're
toasting, I have a toast to propose.

136
00:25:45,396 --> 00:25:48,398
If you cheat, cheat death.

137
00:25:48,399 --> 00:25:50,433
If you steal,
steal the heart of a woman.

138
00:25:50,434 --> 00:25:53,369
If you lie,
lie in the everlasting warmth

139
00:25:53,370 --> 00:25:55,705
of her bosom, and if you drink,

140
00:25:55,706 --> 00:25:57,774
drink with me.

141
00:25:57,775 --> 00:25:59,542
[both slurping]

142
00:26:01,545 --> 00:26:04,114
[exhales]

143
00:26:13,657 --> 00:26:15,425
[liquid pouring]

144
00:26:15,426 --> 00:26:17,360
What did he say?

145
00:26:18,428 --> 00:26:20,763
Perhaps it is getting late.

146
00:26:20,764 --> 00:26:22,799
I think Fuji-sama
appears to be tired.

147
00:26:22,800 --> 00:26:24,200
Fuji-sama...

148
00:26:25,569 --> 00:26:27,504
[Blackthorne]
Oh, nonsense.

149
00:26:28,538 --> 00:26:29,706
Mariko-sama,

150
00:26:29,707 --> 00:26:31,541
ask your husband
if he'd share the...

151
00:26:31,542 --> 00:26:34,344
the story of his escape
in Osaka.

152
00:26:35,545 --> 00:26:38,381
Never too late for a good story.

153
00:26:41,418 --> 00:26:43,486
Well, go on. Ask him, then.

154
00:26:55,532 --> 00:26:57,100
[exhales]

155
00:27:08,211 --> 00:27:10,113
[Buntaro slurps]

156
00:27:32,469 --> 00:27:35,272
He would like to know about
a war you have fought in.

157
00:27:36,306 --> 00:27:37,640
Oh, I don't know.

158
00:27:37,641 --> 00:27:40,510
All of my war stories
are full of holes.

159
00:27:40,511 --> 00:27:42,178
[Mariko]
Please listen.

160
00:27:42,179 --> 00:27:44,414
My husband is tired
and has had a lot to drink.

161
00:27:44,415 --> 00:27:45,782
You must tell him a story.

162
00:27:48,719 --> 00:27:50,487
But choose your words carefully.

163
00:28:02,199 --> 00:28:03,667
[pops lips]

164
00:28:19,683 --> 00:28:21,585
[exhales]

165
00:28:22,586 --> 00:28:24,654
The gateway of your house.

166
00:28:24,655 --> 00:28:26,522
He asks you to choose a post.

167
00:28:26,523 --> 00:28:28,257
What, he's going to shoot it?

168
00:28:28,258 --> 00:28:29,826
The left or the right post?

169
00:28:29,827 --> 00:28:31,628
Well, the man can't
even see straight.

170
00:28:31,629 --> 00:28:34,697
Please choose.

171
00:28:34,698 --> 00:28:36,366
Right?

172
00:28:39,336 --> 00:28:40,503
[Blackthorne]
Mariko-sama.

173
00:28:40,504 --> 00:28:42,205
You should move.

174
00:28:44,574 --> 00:28:46,509
- [gasps]
- Mariko-sama, move.

175
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:47,777
Mariko-sama.

176
00:28:56,386 --> 00:28:58,355
- [thump]
- [gasps]

177
00:29:05,562 --> 00:29:06,796
Mariko-sama.

178
00:29:06,797 --> 00:29:08,498
Get out of the fucking way.

179
00:29:24,748 --> 00:29:26,149
[liquid pouring]

180
00:29:27,651 --> 00:29:30,119
Please tell him

181
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:32,255
that while I understand
that in this country,

182
00:29:32,256 --> 00:29:36,559
like mine, a man's wife
is his property,

183
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:40,129
but I believe strongly

184
00:29:40,130 --> 00:29:42,365
that his wife merits better.

185
00:30:06,523 --> 00:30:08,525
[chuckling]

186
00:30:31,715 --> 00:30:33,516
[Mariko] I am to tell
you about my family.

187
00:30:41,158 --> 00:30:46,096
I am daughter of the late
Lord Akechi Jinsai.

188
00:30:49,166 --> 00:30:51,234
Mariko-sama,
you don't have to do this.

189
00:30:53,870 --> 00:30:56,773
Just make up a story, he'll
never know the difference.

190
00:30:58,208 --> 00:31:03,179
My father's lord
was Kuroda-sama,

191
00:31:03,180 --> 00:31:06,116
ruler of Japan before the <i>Taiko.</i>

192
00:31:10,587 --> 00:31:12,622
Kuroda-sama was corrupt
and murderous,

193
00:31:12,623 --> 00:31:15,725
and so my father killed him
out of love for the realm.

194
00:31:17,160 --> 00:31:20,830
For this he was hunted,
along with my family.

195
00:31:20,831 --> 00:31:25,468
All of my brothers, sisters...

196
00:31:27,137 --> 00:31:28,805
...and my mother...

197
00:31:31,708 --> 00:31:33,576
...they all knelt
before my father,

198
00:31:33,577 --> 00:31:36,479
who was forced to execute them
one by one...

199
00:31:38,148 --> 00:31:40,750
...before committing seppuku
himself.

200
00:31:46,156 --> 00:31:49,326
I was just married
and not permitted to fight.

201
00:31:51,561 --> 00:31:55,565
Each year on the anniversary
of my family's murder,

202
00:31:55,566 --> 00:31:57,834
I ask my husband
to let me take action

203
00:31:57,835 --> 00:32:00,503
against this injustice.

204
00:32:01,838 --> 00:32:03,773
But I can do nothing.

205
00:32:07,844 --> 00:32:10,547
Because my husband
orders me to live.

206
00:32:20,657 --> 00:32:23,493
I ask you to remember
the Eightfold Fence.

207
00:32:30,834 --> 00:32:32,235
Excuse me.

208
00:32:35,539 --> 00:32:36,740
Mariko!

209
00:32:48,418 --> 00:32:51,254
[owl hoots]

210
00:32:51,255 --> 00:32:53,389
[snoring]

211
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:56,125
- [Buntaro grunts]
- [thud]

212
00:32:56,126 --> 00:32:58,194
[Mariko crying]

213
00:33:05,469 --> 00:33:07,504
[thumping]

214
00:33:14,845 --> 00:33:16,412
[panting]

215
00:33:16,413 --> 00:33:18,081
Get out of the way.
I said move, damn you.

216
00:33:19,549 --> 00:33:21,585
Get out of the way.

217
00:33:25,555 --> 00:33:27,690
[Mariko crying]

218
00:33:27,691 --> 00:33:29,726
Get back.

219
00:33:33,664 --> 00:33:36,232
Oh, Christ.

220
00:34:07,664 --> 00:34:09,666
♪ ♪

221
00:34:15,672 --> 00:34:18,174
Buntaro!

222
00:34:18,175 --> 00:34:20,243
Look at me!

223
00:34:39,863 --> 00:34:42,799
♪ ♪

224
00:34:56,713 --> 00:34:58,748
♪ ♪

225
00:35:18,168 --> 00:35:21,638
Oh, what are you doing? Get up.

226
00:35:33,183 --> 00:35:34,751
Sake?!

227
00:35:36,720 --> 00:35:38,622
Is that your excuse?

228
00:35:39,690 --> 00:35:42,292
Get up, you bastard.
On your feet!

229
00:35:42,293 --> 00:35:44,527
[indistinct whispering]

230
00:36:02,546 --> 00:36:04,414
Sake.

231
00:36:05,582 --> 00:36:08,084
You piece of shit.

232
00:36:24,134 --> 00:36:26,136
♪ ♪

233
00:36:35,545 --> 00:36:36,612
[waves crashing]

234
00:36:36,613 --> 00:36:39,249
[seabirds squawking]

235
00:37:13,450 --> 00:37:14,618
[laughs softly]

236
00:37:50,821 --> 00:37:53,089
[insects buzzing]

237
00:38:01,431 --> 00:38:02,598
Morning.

238
00:38:02,599 --> 00:38:04,734
Where is Mariko-sama?

239
00:38:12,642 --> 00:38:14,778
I don't understand anything
you're saying. Where is she?

240
00:38:20,183 --> 00:38:22,185
[horse clopping]

241
00:38:37,434 --> 00:38:39,502
You all right?

242
00:38:44,307 --> 00:38:46,643
All of this is my doing.

243
00:38:47,778 --> 00:38:49,245
Mariko-sama,
your husband's brutality

244
00:38:49,246 --> 00:38:51,314
is no fault of yours.

245
00:38:53,283 --> 00:38:54,784
We should not be seen together.

246
00:38:54,785 --> 00:38:56,486
Oh, the pox on that.

247
00:38:56,487 --> 00:38:58,087
Don't put it behind
that folded fence of yours,

248
00:38:58,088 --> 00:38:59,355
whatever you call it.

249
00:38:59,356 --> 00:39:01,524
I-I see you.
Your disgust for him.

250
00:39:01,525 --> 00:39:03,359
If you want to be free
of that shitless coward,

251
00:39:03,360 --> 00:39:04,594
then be free of him.

252
00:39:04,595 --> 00:39:06,296
Still, you understand so little?

253
00:39:10,567 --> 00:39:12,869
Your swords.

254
00:39:12,870 --> 00:39:14,504
Fuji-sama believes they were
given to her father

255
00:39:14,505 --> 00:39:15,705
as a battle honor.

256
00:39:17,307 --> 00:39:20,410
The truth is, he died a coward,
begging for his life.

257
00:39:20,411 --> 00:39:22,211
Her grandfather bought them
from a drunken samurai

258
00:39:22,212 --> 00:39:25,281
for three bags of rice
to spare her the embarrassment.

259
00:39:25,282 --> 00:39:28,484
But she knows nothing
and we say nothing,

260
00:39:28,485 --> 00:39:31,421
because our silence
is what she merits.

261
00:39:36,293 --> 00:39:40,196
I will give my husband nothing,

262
00:39:40,197 --> 00:39:43,266
not even my hatred,

263
00:39:43,267 --> 00:39:45,735
because that is what he merits.

264
00:39:45,736 --> 00:39:47,771
♪ ♪

265
00:39:51,241 --> 00:39:54,143
It's a good story, Mariko-sama,

266
00:39:54,144 --> 00:39:57,413
and I understand the sentiment,
but you take it too far.

267
00:39:57,414 --> 00:39:59,682
Honestly, you're shuffling
around with your manners

268
00:39:59,683 --> 00:40:01,751
and your buried self, for what?

269
00:40:03,754 --> 00:40:06,589
I would not expect
for you to understand.

270
00:40:06,590 --> 00:40:08,625
Well, forgive me, but you'd
die to avenge your father,

271
00:40:08,626 --> 00:40:11,628
you'd live in anguish
to spite your husband.

272
00:40:11,629 --> 00:40:14,364
Which is it?
What becomes of you?

273
00:40:16,366 --> 00:40:20,470
My life is mine
and yours is yours.

274
00:40:21,805 --> 00:40:24,874
If you can't see that,

275
00:40:24,875 --> 00:40:27,477
you'll never be free
of this prison.

276
00:40:30,147 --> 00:40:33,149
No, Anjin-sama.

277
00:40:33,150 --> 00:40:36,219
It is you who is imprisoned.

278
00:40:36,220 --> 00:40:38,822
If freedom is all
you ever life for...

279
00:40:40,791 --> 00:40:43,560
...you will never be free
of yourself.

280
00:40:48,165 --> 00:40:52,101
I will honor my duty
as your translator.

281
00:40:52,102 --> 00:40:54,404
But from this day forward,

282
00:40:54,405 --> 00:40:57,340
the only words we share
will be from others' lips.

283
00:41:19,496 --> 00:41:21,498
[sobbing]

284
00:41:34,778 --> 00:41:36,780
What's the matter with everyone?

285
00:41:42,152 --> 00:41:43,720
What is it?

286
00:41:49,526 --> 00:41:50,827
Pheasant?

287
00:42:00,637 --> 00:42:03,673
Our gardener?

288
00:42:03,674 --> 00:42:05,274
Old bastard should get a medal

289
00:42:05,275 --> 00:42:07,177
just for being able
to climb up there.

290
00:42:08,245 --> 00:42:10,213
It's fine.

291
00:42:10,214 --> 00:42:12,315
It'd been up there
long enough anyway.

292
00:42:40,310 --> 00:42:42,078
What have you done?

293
00:42:45,515 --> 00:42:48,084
You put that old man to death

294
00:42:48,085 --> 00:42:51,220
over a stinking,

295
00:42:51,221 --> 00:42:53,156
God-cursed pheasant?

296
00:42:54,825 --> 00:42:56,359
[sniffles]

297
00:42:58,829 --> 00:43:01,197
What the hell is wrong with you?

298
00:43:04,801 --> 00:43:07,370
Why in Christ's name
didn't you ask me?

299
00:43:20,384 --> 00:43:22,085
Go away.

300
00:43:25,555 --> 00:43:27,090
All of you!

301
00:43:31,695 --> 00:43:33,196
Go away!

302
00:43:43,840 --> 00:43:46,076
[birds chirping]

303
00:44:22,646 --> 00:44:24,614
Lord, when we were at sea,

304
00:44:24,615 --> 00:44:28,117
we discussed my training
your army in European combat.

305
00:44:28,118 --> 00:44:31,254
I feel I have now fulfilled
that duty.

306
00:44:31,255 --> 00:44:33,790
I ask that my ship and my men

307
00:44:33,791 --> 00:44:36,225
be returned to me
so that I may leave

308
00:44:36,226 --> 00:44:37,761
and not return.

309
00:45:06,123 --> 00:45:08,391
He asks what troubles you.

310
00:45:08,392 --> 00:45:11,494
I'm troubled
by your whole damned country.

311
00:45:12,562 --> 00:45:14,664
Life has no value to you.

312
00:45:14,665 --> 00:45:17,767
Only the meaningless rituals
you are trapped in.

313
00:45:19,236 --> 00:45:22,205
Like Uejirou.

314
00:45:22,206 --> 00:45:24,608
Who died for nothing.

315
00:45:32,849 --> 00:45:34,584
It is my understanding
that you ordered

316
00:45:34,585 --> 00:45:36,386
no one to touch that bird.

317
00:45:36,387 --> 00:45:38,655
And by law, your house
could not disobey that order.

318
00:45:38,656 --> 00:45:40,089
Nor could they allow
the rotting pheasant

319
00:45:40,090 --> 00:45:41,224
to ruin the peace
of the village.

320
00:45:41,225 --> 00:45:43,393
The bird meant nothing to me.

321
00:45:43,394 --> 00:45:45,729
Your words gave it meaning.

322
00:45:47,364 --> 00:45:49,499
[horse neighing in distance]

323
00:45:57,774 --> 00:45:59,509
A meeting was called
with Muraji,

324
00:45:59,510 --> 00:46:01,244
who is the village headman,

325
00:46:01,245 --> 00:46:03,246
but he determined
it was a house problem.

326
00:46:03,247 --> 00:46:06,282
So someone had to steal it
and bury it.

327
00:46:06,283 --> 00:46:07,517
Uejirou announced
that he had been sick lately,

328
00:46:07,518 --> 00:46:09,552
so he volunteered.

329
00:46:10,754 --> 00:46:12,622
He died for a great purpose.

330
00:46:12,623 --> 00:46:15,725
It was a better end
than he could have hoped for.

331
00:46:15,726 --> 00:46:18,528
♪ ♪

332
00:46:18,529 --> 00:46:20,297
I killed him.

333
00:46:23,233 --> 00:46:25,302
Lord forgive me,
I killed that old man.

334
00:46:27,270 --> 00:46:29,539
There is no use dwelling
on what cannot be undone.

335
00:46:29,540 --> 00:46:31,507
How can you believe that?

336
00:46:31,508 --> 00:46:36,279
We live and we die.

337
00:46:36,280 --> 00:46:38,681
We control nothing beyond that.

338
00:46:38,682 --> 00:46:41,217
- [birds squawking]
- [low rumble]

339
00:46:44,655 --> 00:46:45,755
[rocks crashing]

340
00:46:45,756 --> 00:46:47,824
[distant shouting]

341
00:46:52,696 --> 00:46:55,332
[rumbling intensifies]

342
00:46:58,568 --> 00:47:00,470
[panting]

343
00:47:08,512 --> 00:47:10,246
[shouting continues]

344
00:47:22,559 --> 00:47:24,227
Jesus!

345
00:47:25,262 --> 00:47:27,230
Where the hell is he?

346
00:47:29,433 --> 00:47:30,500
[grunts]

347
00:47:45,816 --> 00:47:47,350
He's here!

348
00:47:55,158 --> 00:47:56,693
[exclaims]
There he is!

349
00:48:00,664 --> 00:48:01,831
[all grunting]

350
00:48:03,834 --> 00:48:06,603
[panting]

351
00:48:10,507 --> 00:48:12,242
[coughing]

352
00:48:15,245 --> 00:48:17,480
[wheezing]

353
00:48:17,481 --> 00:48:19,516
[gasps]

354
00:48:27,424 --> 00:48:29,459
[panting]

355
00:48:48,311 --> 00:48:50,413
These belonged to Fuji's father.

356
00:48:50,414 --> 00:48:52,382
They may not be much,

357
00:48:52,383 --> 00:48:55,418
but I'd be honored
if he would accept this gift.

358
00:48:59,389 --> 00:49:01,424
[laughs]

359
00:49:26,383 --> 00:49:28,351
♪ ♪

360
00:49:38,562 --> 00:49:40,597
